    {
      "id": "PopularPost85926",
      "post_content": "So, in Kamigawa, they added the Arcane type to a well-known card, and usually upped the cost or otherwise nerfed it. Then, it would stand to reason that removing the Arcane type would make a card cheaper, right? ... Right?  \n  \n[Shock](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shock) gains the Arcane type and a Splice ability, and becomes the more-expensive [Glacial Ray](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Glacial Ray).  \n[Boomerang](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boomerang) gains the Arcane type and becomes a Sorcery instead of an Instant, and is [Eye of Nowhere](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Eye of Nowhere).  \n[Desperate Ritual](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Desperate Ritual) loses the Arcane type and Splice ability... and costs the same. :(",
      "posted_by": "tenkaze",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost85926\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">So, in Kamigawa, they added the Arcane type to a well-known card, and usually upped the cost or otherwise nerfed it. Then, it would stand to reason that removing the Arcane type would make a card cheaper, right? ... Right?<br/><br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Shock\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shock\">Shock</a> gains the Arcane type and a Splice ability, and becomes the more-expensive <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Glacial Ray\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Glacial Ray\">Glacial Ray</a>.<br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Boomerang\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Boomerang\">Boomerang</a> gains the Arcane type and becomes a Sorcery instead of an Instant, and is <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Eye of Nowhere\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Eye of Nowhere\">Eye of Nowhere</a>.<br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Desperate Ritual\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Desperate Ritual\">Desperate Ritual</a> loses the Arcane type and Splice ability... and costs the same. :(</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '85926'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy4059\">tenkaze</span>\r\